nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If the response is truncated, Amazon Q Business returns this token. You can use this token in a subsequent request to retrieve the next set of applications.

nested_items.name: applications
nested_items.description: An array of summary information on the configuration of one or more Amazon Q Business applications.

nested_items.name: displayName
nested_items.description: The name of the Amazon Q Business application.

nested_items.name: applicationId
nested_items.description: The identifier for the Amazon Q Business application.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp when the Amazon Q Business application was created.

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp when the Amazon Q Business application was last updated.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the Amazon Q Business application. The application is ready to use when the status is ACTIVE.

nested_items.name: identityType
nested_items.description: The authentication type being used by a Amazon Q Business application.

nested_items.name: quickSightConfiguration
nested_items.description: The Amazon QuickSight configuration for an Amazon Q Business application that uses QuickSight as the identity provider.

nested_items.name: clientNamespace
nested_items.description: The Amazon QuickSight namespace that is used as the identity provider. For more information about QuickSight namespaces, see Namespace operations.
